# Project: FilmFinder - Application de Recherche de Films

## Code Style
- Language: JavaScript (ES6+)
- No frameworks: Vanilla JavaScript only
- Styling: Tailwind CSS (via CDN)
- Icons: Font Awesome (via CDN)

## Naming Conventions
- Functions: camelCase (fetchMovies, handleSearch)
- Variables: camelCase (currentPage, isLoading)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (API_KEY, API_URL)
- DOM Elements: camelCase or kebab-case (searchInput, filmModal)
- CSS Classes: Tailwind utility classes, kebab-case for custom classes (film-card, animated-orb)

## Patterns to Use
✅ ES6+ features (const/let, arrow functions, async/await)
✅ Fetch API for HTTP requests
✅ Intersection Observer for scroll animations
✅ Event delegation when appropriate
✅ Error handling with try/catch
✅ Modular functions (single responsibility)
✅ Comments in French for documentation

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid
❌ Don't use `var` (use `const` or `let`)
❌ Don't use `==` (use `===`)
❌ Don't mutate DOM directly multiple times (batch updates)
❌ Don't use `console.log` in production code (use only for debugging)
❌ Don't create global variables (use modules or closures)
❌ Don't ignore errors (always handle them)

## File Structure
- HTML: `index.html` (single page application)
- JavaScript: `script.js` (all logic in one file for simplicity)
- CSS: `styles.css` (custom styles + animations)
- Config: `config.js` (API configuration - not committed)

## API Integration
- Always check API response status
- Handle errors gracefully with user-friendly messages
- Validate input before API calls
- Use environment/config for API keys (never hardcode)

## UI/UX Patterns
- Show loading states during API calls
- Display error messages clearly
- Provide feedback for user actions
- Use Intersection Observer for progressive loading
- Implement infinite scroll for pagination
- Glassmorphism design with modern color palette (2025-2026)

## Animation Guidelines
- Use CSS transitions for smooth animations
- Intersection Observer for scroll-triggered animations
- Keep animations subtle (opacity, transform, blur)
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion if implemented

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Provide alt text for images
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Maintain good color contrast ratios (WCAG AA minimum)

## Documentation
- Add JSDoc comments for complex functions
- Document API endpoints and responses
- Keep README.md updated with changes
- Comment complex logic in French

## Security
- Never commit API keys (use config.js)
- Validate all user input
- Sanitize data from API responses
- Use HTTPS for API calls
